annotation.TEXT: Well, thanks to that Goomba, I've traded my reserve flower for an extra cape. I guess that's fine. And now, normal speed bonus game which I hopefully won't screw up this time!
Swimsuit Mania (Normal) (or "Swimsuit Edition" if you prefer)
Okay, hang onto this cape!
Yes, got all of the coins that time!
By the way, I'm going to try to remember to cut out most of each lengthy "loading" period from now on, just like I did there. (The "loading" actually took about 2Â½ seconds longer than what you saw.)
Hey, can I jump through that gap in the ceiling there?
Okay, let's not screw up with the P-switch this time.
Whoa, I think I got lucky there.
Don't want to finish off the spell card quite yet...
Hi, Yoshi!
Yeah, I can't get to the P-switch now. Whoops. Well, I'll just do it right on my next trip through the level.
So, yeah, as that sepia tone flashback showed, I did indeed hit the midpoint bar just after taking that dumb hit. So, why didn't the midpoint entrance work?
Alright, this does appear to be the title demo level, so we should already know what to expect for the most part in this area.
And that was on the Easy difficulty level!
(Gasp!) MOON! MOON! MOOOONNN!!!
Okay, everything from here on out is new, since the title demo didn't go this far. (What would happen if the title demo went through a screen transition?)
This is highly inconvenient, because I just lost both Yoshi and my cape to that stupid mole, so now I've gotta take the time to get them back.

Just a mushroom? Oh, maybe that's where the midpoint entrance is. (And similarly, I bet the midpoint entrance in the Easy version was supposed to be above the ice block at the bottom of that similar shaft. Well, that would've complicated things a bit if I actually did start there with Yoshi as I was intending to do.)
There's the key, which is why I needed a cape.
Yeah, I'm just teleporting those 1-ups into my pocket or something up there. It's a little-known special power of Mario's, which is pretty much completely useless.
Whoa, lots of bullet cannons, which really want to separate me from Yoshi. Well, I'm not gonna let 'em!
Bah, missed a coin. My OCD is gonna drive me nuts now.
Okay, I have my cape back, so that last little incident didn't really cost me anything.
Well, there's a 1-up I didn't even see. Okay, I'm going to assume that those black blocks are bad... as in "instant death" bad!
Well, if Yoshi had been assassinated there, I would've gotten a new one here.
Okay, I'm going to get Yoshi here, then Start+Select out and reenter the level at midpoint, which is right near a cape block.
Barf!
The large white number is the amount of graze gotten in the current chapter, and the small number underneath it is the total amount of graze gotten in the whole game.
Warp Star (Translation provided by Teradramon Teradramon.)
Ohhh... Nuts... I think I screwed up.
Zwee!
Be careful of the moles, of course.
That went well. I think the lag helped me out a bit there.
Yep, it links straight to the Easy side of things. Also, I guess Crystal Cave (Normal) is a "no auto-move" level, since I didn't automatically move after revealing that path.
You're the Star!
Whoa, I actually managed to save him there!
Whoa, that was weird! So, apparently, I can grab the 1-ups down there while I'm off the top of the screen!
I bet the fifth Yoshi coin is way up there, and I've gotta hurry to reach it in time.
Alright, I'll be coming back here later (probably when you guys inevitably vote for that level).
Alright, that's the end of the level-breaking, and I think this is about where the title demo had ended.
Barf!
Alright, now to go back through that level for the secret exit, at mostly ludicrous speed!
These creepy Mario Paint smileys are obviously footballs in disguise.
There we go! And since I have a cape, victory dive bombs are a must!
And there's the goal. Also, shut up, clock. (Oh, darn. I forgot to pause during the hurry up sound effect, which somebody voted for me to do earlier. I've gotta remember to do that at some point.)
And there's the keyhole. And no, I can't just spit it into the keyhole like that. (It would've been interesting if keyhole exits worked that way, though.)
Whoa, that mole was trying to stealthily assassinate Yoshi while I wasn't paying attention! However, I actually was paying attention, so he gets assassinated instead!
I didn't unexpectedly bounce off of any of those Ninjis while slide-killing them.
Okay, fine. I'll do it this way.
Alright, I got all of the Yoshi coins.
Oh, and from what I saw with my accidental sneak peek last time, I should probably hold right when the level begins.
Oh, I see. I need this P-switch to disarm this classic Kaizo trap.
~ Advice ~ 1. Get careless when you go into the next room and you're toast, ze! 2. Watch out for that goal! "Is that sooo?"
Yep, I think I see why I've gotta recycle it.
Oh, that log up there is totally solid. Can't jump through it from below.
Okay, this time, let's not trust those evil, evil coins. (Well, I can trust the ones towards the top that I can safely grab.)
Zwee!
Classic Ocean (Easy)
ARGH!!! Well, that just happened... Bye, Yoshi!
Okay, so we've got a larger Boo from Yoshi's Island, and there's the P-switch that I assume that I've gotta recycle.
By the way, if you guys are about to comment about whether I did hit midpoint there or not, watch the rest of the video first.
Oh, what the heck? Why did I bounce off of that fourth Ninji after sliding through the first three without bouncing?
Now, I'm going to head to Crystal Cave (Normal), since I don't want this to be a "1 video video".
Bonus game average so far: 12 / 2 = 6 1-ups each.
Whoa, we're auto-scrolling here!
BGM: Super Marisa Land - Underground Stage
However, I think I'm going to go back and do the level the proper way.
Anything up above that turn block? It seems like a place to hide something good.
Yeah, the status bar looks kind of lousy, as someone mentioned.
~ Key-Goal Hint ~ 1. Yoshi's a necessity 2. A cape is a necessity 3. Use the P-Switch-reusing trick "Is that sooo?"
Yep, that was indeed the midpoint entrance, which does work correctly in this level.
Forget it. I'll let that ceiling plant live.
Umm... Boo, could you not interfere, please?
Zwee!
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 2 - Run, Rambi! Run!
I'm guessing this shortcut was intentionally made available, because of this shaft with the ice block at the bottom of it.
(+2 coins, since I guess the P-switch ended just before the fadeout completely finished.)
I'm still going to go over the top here, though. Then I'll backtrack to get a cape and Yoshi.
Oh, it's this map again.
Alright, you guys have seen what three levels are available. So, where should I go next? You're the Star!, Classic Ocean (Easy), or Swimsuit Mania/Edition (Normal)? Place your votes now!
Sacrificial horse count: 1
Okay, I lost my flower to that dumb hit, but that's unimportant, as long as I don't make any more mistakes.
Is that a bullet cannon? ...Yep.
Okay, so I have this P-switch...
Thwimps? Diagonal Podoboos? Why are they here? Well, at least Yoshi can eat the diagonal Podoboos.
Total graze from that spell card: OVER 9000!!! (9689, to be exact.)
Okay, let me get my cape here...
Well, so much for hanging onto the cape...
There's the cape. Now I just need the P-switch that I'll be recycling, and I'll be all set.
Just made it! Wow, two close calls in a row!
I should probably kill a few things over there to reduce the lag.

Anything up and to the left? Well, I'm not gonna bother checking now. (However, I checked off camera later, and there's nothing of interest over there, and also, those black blocks are indeed instant death.)
Graze
Zwee!
Oh, geez! NOOOOO!!!

The midpoint bar even returned there, as if I didn't hit it. So, here are my theories: Either the midpoint bar was inserted as a Map16 tile and the midpoint entrance was erroneously set to screen 0, or there's some ASM that cancels out the midpoint hit when I Start+Select out.
Wait, what am I doing back at the beginning? I did hit midpoint back there, right?
...Really, game? Following that line of coins just leads to my death? Well, at least I got all of the Yoshi coins before that happened.
I have a feeling my cape will be really valuable here. Try not to lose it in some dumb way this time.
Ooh, sparkly.
Ah, nuts. I guess I gotta say "Bye, Yoshi!" here. (However, this doesn't count as a sacrificial horse this time, since he didn't fall into a pit or anything like that.)
Yay, a fish, and not a Podoboo. (For some reason, the sprite that comes out of the P-switch with this glitch is a Podoboo in VLDC 8.)
Also, Yoshi is helpful too. Try not to lose him in some dumb way this time.
Goal tape average so far: 220 / 6 = 36.667 stars each.
Okay, so Crystal Cave (Easy) it is!
Okay, I've made my way back here the regular way.
I wonder if this midpoint is functional...
Zwee!
Aha! So, is this the easy secret exit that links me to the Easy path that I'd heard about?

Alright, gimme a moment to make my way back there...

Okay, so I need Yoshi and a cape, and I'll need to make use of the P-switch recycling glitch in order to reach the secret exit, I take it.

Most likely. Huh, what are those black blocks over there?
